claims:
1. A system comprising:
a database coupled to a network and storing a plurality of instructions, comprising a Hurst coefficient, average correct on first try percent, average test score, average homework score, average part score, number of attempted parts, average number of attempted parts, or average number of attempts per part, for generating a plurality of first level features from a user input;
a server comprising a computing device coupled to a network and comprising at least one processor executing instructions within a memory which, when executed, cause the system to:
receive, through the network from a user of a client device, a user input;
generate, from the user input, a plurality of first level features according to the plurality of instructions;
generate a plurality of second level features from an aggregation of the plurality of first level features over a plurality of sequential predetermined times;
identify:
a second level feature set comprising:
portions of the plurality of first level features and the plurality of the second level features, and
a first shared attribute between the user and a plurality of users of a plurality of additional client devices;
a second shared attribute between the second level feature set and a plurality of additional second level feature sets;
an anomaly in the second level feature set; and
a risk based on the identified anomaly, wherein the risk is non-specific to the user of the client device;
input the second level feature set, the second shared attribute, and the risk into a machine learning classifier and
generate, as an output from a machine-learning classifier, a risk prediction.
2. The system of claim 1, wherein the instructions further cause the system to:
generate a plurality of additional first level features from a plurality of additional user inputs;
aggregate the plurality of additional first level features over the plurality of sequential predetermined times to produce a second aggregation of the plurality of additional first level features; and
generate a plurality of additional second level features based on the second aggregation.
3. The system of claim 2, wherein the instructions further cause the system to aggregate the plurality of first level features until a minimum number of the plurality of first level features has been aggregated.
4. The system of claim 3, wherein the instructions further cause the system to generate the plurality of second level features when the minimum number of the plurality of first level features has been aggregated.
5. The system of claim 1, wherein the instructions further cause the system to transmit, through the network for display on a second client device, an alert based on the risk prediction, wherein the alert comprises a graphical depiction of the risk prediction.
6. The system of claim 1, wherein the instructions further cause the system to generate the plurality of first level features and the plurality of second level features at an end of each of the plurality of sequential predetermined times.
